  "body": "CL can send tons of logs, and as an effect, we have logs like on the below screen.\r\n![Screenshot from 2023-06-02 17-04-16](https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/assets/9356351/6c73e1bb-200b-43f0-81f1-20c09c8970b1)\r\n\r\nIt would be better to filter them.\r\n\r\nAn alternative solution would be add a config option. We could introduce a new setting: JsonRpc.Logs with the following values (just an example):\r\n```\r\nNone (future default option nr 1)\r\nEnginePortRequest\r\nEnginePortRequestAndResponse\r\nNonEnginePortsRequest (future default option nr 2)\r\nNonEnginePortsRequestAndResponse\r\nAllRequest (current option)\r\nAll\r\n\r\n```\r\nIt might be useful for debugging (for example hive tests). Of course, we can configure JsonRpc logs in Nlog, but it is not convenient enough",
